  "text": "f . Eq. (30) then reveals thatf π = f π in the chiral limit, which result is well-known from the axial anomaly analysis. Although the chiral limit formula (30) can be applied without reservations only to pions, it is customary to write the amplitudes for η 8 , η 0 → γγ in the same form as [CITATION_1] , defining thereby the γγ-decay constantsf η 8 andf η 0 :",
